# MinIO IAM split — memory-server's scoped user password.
# ADR-048 PR-B7 (the parser-exploit close).
#
# This user is bound to the `audittrace_app` policy provisioned by
# `charts/audittrace/templates/minio/job-bucket-init.yaml`:
#   PUT      quarantine/*       (allowed — that's where uploads land)
#   GET/DEL  quarantine/*       (DENIED — pre-scanned bytes are off-limits)
#   * on episodic/*, procedural/*, trust-store/*  (allowed — legacy paths)
#
# The DENY on GET quarantine/* is the IAM-level enforcement that
# closes the parser-exploit gap. PR-B2's Python `QuarantineDenyingMinioClient`
# remains as defense-in-depth.
#
# 1. Generate a strong password (`openssl rand -base64 32`).
# 2. Save as ./secrets/minio_audittrace_app_password.txt.
# 3. Run `make k8s-bootstrap-secrets`. Lands at:
#    - Vault: kv/audittrace/minio/audittrace_app (key: password)
#    - k8s Secret: <release>-minio-iam (audittrace_app_password)
REPLACE_WITH_STRONG_PASSWORD
